claim.claim-text:
1. A print device for obtaining print content for a client device, the print device comprising: 
a wireless communications port for receiving a reference from the client, said reference comprising at least a location corresponding to the print content; 
a network communications port for communicating with the location; 
a memory storing executable program instructions; and, 
a processor for executing said stored program instructions, said instructions when executed by said processor for causing said wireless communications port to accept a communications link from a client and accept said reference communicated from said client over said link, for causing said network communications port to obtain the print content from said location.

18. A print device for printing content at the request of a portable device, the print device comprising: 
a wireless communications port for supporting radio frequency communications; 
a network communications port for communicating with a network; 
a memory storing executable program instructions and printer capabilities; 
a processor for executing said stored program instructions, said instructions when executed by said processor for causing the print device to: 
accept a reference communicated from the portable device over said wireless link, said reference comprising print server and print content network addresses; 
communicate said reference to said print server using said network communications port; 
retrieve said printer capabilities from said memory and to communicate said capabilities over said network communications port to said print server; and 
transmit instructions to said print server to communicate the print content to the print device using said network communications port.

21. A program product for causing a print device to print content at the request of a client, the program product comprising executable instructions embedded in a computer readable medium that when executed cause the print device to: 
accept a wireless communications link from the client; 
accept a reference input over said wireless communications link from the client, said reference comprising at least a location corresponding to the print content; 
communicate with said location; 
obtain the print content from said location; and, 
print the print content.

40. A program product for causing a print device to output print content at the request of a portable device, the printer of the type that has a wireless communications port, a network communications port, a memory, and a processor, the program product comprising executable instructions embedded in a computer readable medium that when executed cause the print device to: 
accept a wireless communications link from the portable device via a radio frequency signal over the wireless communications port; 
accept a reference input over said wireless communications link from the portable device, said reference comprising at least a network address corresponding to the print content and a print server network address; 
communicate an acknowledgement to the portable device over said wireless communications link; 
establish a server communications link with said print server at said print server network address over the network communications port, communicate said reference to said print server over said server communications link; 
retrieve stored printer capabilities from the print device memory and communicate said printer capabilities to said print server over said server communications link; 
communicate instructions to said print server for communicating the print content to the print device; 
accept an interrupt signal from the portable device over said wireless communications link and to communicate data responsive to said interrupt signal to the portable device over said wireless communications link; and, 
print the print content.
